一些会飛的昆蟲（例如[[蝗蟲|蝗蟲]]，某些[[蝴蝶|蝴蝶]]和[[蜻蜓|蜻蜓]]）皆具有很強的飛行力，它們可以長距離遷徙。在蜻蜓中，[[小斑蜻|小斑蜻]]和[[赤蜻屬|赤蜻屬]]因大規模遷徙而聞名<ref name =Williams1957>{{cite journal |author=Williams, C. B. |title=Insect Migration |journal=Annual Review of Entomology |volume=2 |pages=163–180 |year=1957 |doi=10.1146/annurev.en.02.010157.001115 |issue=1}}</ref>，而[[印度|印度]]的[[薄翅蜻蜓|薄翅蜻蜓]]更是印度和[[非洲|非洲]]之間最長的越洋昆蟲，遷徙距離最長可达7,081公里<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chinatimes.com/realtimenews/20160305002539-260408?chdtv|title=新昆蟲界超馬好手 蜻蜓竟可遷徙7千公里|website=中時新聞網|date=2016-03-05|access-date=2020-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200804100345/https://www.chinatimes.com/realtimenews/20160305002539-260408?chdtv|archive-date=2020-08-04|dead-url=no}}</ref>。而在1988年10月，[[沙漠蝗蟲|沙漠蝗蟲]]在[[熱帶輻合帶|熱帶輻合帶]]中利用氣流向西飛過[[大西洋|大西洋]]4,500公里<ref>{{cite web |last=Tipping |first=Christopher |title=Chapter 11: The Longest Migration |url=http://www.entnemdept.ufl.edu/walker/ufbir/chapters/chapter_11.shtml |publisher=Department of Entomology & Nematology University of Florida |accessdate=2014-09-08 |date=1995-05-08 |dead-url=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924001116/http://www.entnemdept.ufl.edu/walker/ufbir/chapters/chapter_11.shtml |archivedate=2015-09-24 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://env.people.com.cn/BIG5/n1/2020/0323/c1010-31643839.html|title=防治沙漠蝗 中國緊鑼密鼓|website=人民網|date=2020-03-23|access-date=2020-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200804153731/http://env.people.com.cn/BIG5/n1/2020/0323/c1010-31643839.html|archive-date=2020-08-04|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[君主斑蝶|君主斑蝶]]每年都會約在8月向南遷徙4,750公里，並於春天北回<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nature.com/scitable/knowledge/library/animal-migration-13259533/|title=Animal Migration - Learn Science at Scitable|website=www.nature.com|accessdate=2020-08-06|archive-date=2020-08-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200802081018/https://www.nature.com/scitable/knowledge/library/animal-migration-13259533/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，但在2019年6月刊於《[[美國國家科學院院刊|美國國家科學院院刊]]》的研究發現，不論是完全人工飼養的君主斑蝶後代，以及父母親為野生君主斑蝶的後代，只要曾被放於室內繁殖，牠們均會失去遷徙能力<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestandnews.com/cosmos/%E4%BF%9D%E8%82%B2%E5%85%A9%E9%9B%A3-%E5%90%9B%E4%B8%BB%E6%96%91%E8%9D%B6%E6%9B%BE%E9%80%B2%E5%AE%A4%E5%85%A7%E5%8D%B3%E4%B8%8D%E6%87%82%E8%BE%A8%E5%88%A5%E9%81%B7%E5%BE%99%E6%96%B9%E5%90%91/|title=【保育兩難】君主斑蝶曾進室內即不懂辨別遷徙方向|website=立場新聞|date=2019-06-25|accessdate=2020-08-06|archive-date=2019-08-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815075446/https://thestandnews.com/cosmos/%E4%BF%9D%E8%82%B2%E5%85%A9%E9%9B%A3-%E5%90%9B%E4%B8%BB%E6%96%91%E8%9D%B6%E6%9B%BE%E9%80%B2%E5%AE%A4%E5%85%A7%E5%8D%B3%E4%B8%8D%E6%87%82%E8%BE%A8%E5%88%A5%E9%81%B7%E5%BE%99%E6%96%B9%E5%90%91/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===哺乳類===
[[File:Wildebeest-during-Great-Migration.JPG|thumb]]正進行大規模的遷徙]]
一些[[哺乳類|哺乳類]]動物也會表現出非凡的遷徙，在[[北美洲|北美洲]]的[[馴鹿|馴鹿]]是世界上陸地遷徙距離較長的哺乳動物之一，每年達到4,868公里。但[[灰狼|灰狼]]的遷徙距離比馴鹿更多，其累計總距離為7,247公里<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Joly |first1=Kyle |last2=Gurarie |first2=Eliezer |last3=Sorum |first3=Mathew S. |last4=Kaczensky |first4=Petra |last5=Cameron |first5=Matthew D. |last6=Jakes |first6=Andrew F. |last7=Borg |first7=Bridget L. |last8=Nandintsetseg |first8=Dejid |last9=Hopcraft |first9=J. Grant C. |last10=Buuveibaatar |first10=Bayarbaatar |last11=Jones |first11=Paul F. |date=December 2019 |title=Longest terrestrial migrations and movements around the world |journal=Scientific Reports |volume=9 |issue=1 |pages=15333 |doi=10.1038/s41598-019-51884-5 |issn=2045-2322 |pmc=6814704 |pmid=31654045|bibcode=2019NatSR...915333J }}</ref>。在[[塞倫蓋蒂|塞倫蓋蒂]]的“動物大遷徙”中，大約有170萬隻[[牛羚|牛羚]]和成千上萬的大型獵物，包括[[瞪羚|瞪羚]]和[[斑馬|斑馬]]，皆会參與其中<ref name="ngorongoro">{{cite web |url=http://www.ngorongorotanzania.com/get-there.html |title=How to Get There, Ngorongoro Crater |publisher=Ngorongoro Crater Tanzania |year=2013 |accessdate=2014-06-19 |dead-url=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140322061200/http://www.ngorongorotanzania.com/get-there.html |archivedate=2014-03-22 }}</ref><ref name="UNESCO">{{cite web |url=https://whc.unesco.org/en/list/39 |title=Ngorongoro Conservation Area |publisher=United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization – World Heritage Centre |accessdate=2014-06-19 |dead-url=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140612001605/https://whc.unesco.org/en/list/39 |archivedate=2014-06-12 }}</ref>。在2009年的一項文獻調查發現，有20多個物種曾經參與大規模遷徙<ref>{{cite journal |author=Grant Harris |display-authors=et al |title=Global decline in aggregated migrations of large terrestrial mammals |journal=Endangered Species Research |volume=7 |pages=55–76 |date=Apr 2009 |doi=10.3354/esr00173 |url=https://www.int-res.com/articles/esr2009/7/n007p055.pdf |access-date=2020-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206161249/http://www.int-res.com/articles/esr2009/7/n007p055.pdf |archive-date=2019-12-06 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，但在這些動物中，[[跳羚|跳羚]]、[[白尾角馬|白尾角馬]]、[[羚羊|羚羊]]和[[土庫曼野驢|土庫曼野驢]]的遷徙已停止<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Penny van Oosterzee |title=Wildebeest no more: The death of Africa's great migrations |journal=New Scientist |date=2017-12-09 |url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg23631550-700-wildebeest-no-more-the-death-of-africas-great-migrations |author= |access-date=2020-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200728040357/https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg23631550-700-wildebeest-no-more-the-death-of-africas-great-migrations/ |archive-date=2020-07-28 |dead-url=no }} Cites Harris et al. See [https://d1o50x50snmhul.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mg31550701.jpg figure] {{Wayback|url=https://d1o50x50snmhul.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mg31550701.jpg |date=20171208174820 }}.</ref>。一些蝙蝠亦會出現長距離遷徙，以在[[俄勒岡州|俄勒岡州]]和[[墨西哥|墨西哥]]南部之間繁殖的{{tsl|en|Mexican free-tailed bat|墨西哥遊離尾蝠}}最为著名<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.batconservation.org/about-bats/natural-history/bats-migration |title=Bats & Migration |publisher=Organization for Bat Conservation |accessdate=2014-06-19 |dead-url=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140614131413/http://www.batconservation.org/about-bats/natural-history/bats-migration |archivedate=2014-06-14 }}</ref>。此外，遷徙在[[鯨魚|鯨魚]]和[[海豚|海豚]]等[[鯨類|鯨類]]動物中亦佔有重要的席位<ref>Lockyer, C.H. and Brown, S.G. ''The Migration of Whales''. pp. 105–137 in Aidley, 1981.</ref>。

===其他動物===
一些[[爬行動物|爬行動物]]和[[兩棲動物|兩棲動物]]也會進行遷徙<ref>{{cite book |publisher=Springer |author1=Russell, A. P. |title=Migration of Organisms |url=https://archive.org/details/migrationoforgan0000unse |author2=Bauer, A. M. |author3=Johnson, M. K. |year=2005 |pages=[https://archive.org/details/migrationoforgan0000unse/page/151 151]–203 |editor=Ashraf, M. T. |doi=10.1007/3-540-26604-6_7 |isbn=978-3-540-26603-7 }}</ref>，例如[[響尾蛇|響尾蛇]]在春季会從巢穴中爬出來作遷徙，尋找夏季棲息地，以便在開闊的地區尋覓食物<ref name=geo>{{cite web|url=https://www.nationalgeographic.com/magazine/2010/11/great-migrations/|title=Animal Migrations|date=2010-11-01|website=National Geographic Magazine|accessdate=2020-08-06|archive-date=2020-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200810041842/https://www.nationalgeographic.com/magazine/2010/11/great-migrations/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://sina.com.hk/news/article/20200619/0/0/2/%E9%9F%BF%E5%B0%BE%E8%9B%87%E6%95%B8%E9%87%8F%E4%BB%A5%E9%A9%9A%E4%BA%BA%E9%80%9F%E5%BA%A6%E6%B8%9B%E5%B0%91%E8%88%87%E4%BA%BA%E9%A1%9E%E6%B4%BB%E5%8B%95%E6%81%AF%E6%81%AF%E7%9B%B8%E9%97%9C-11812700.html|title=響尾蛇數量以驚人速度減少，與人類活動息息相關！|website=香港新浪|accessdate=2020-08-06|archive-date=2020-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200810041428/https://sina.com.hk/news/article/20200619/0/0/2/%E9%9F%BF%E5%B0%BE%E8%9B%87%E6%95%B8%E9%87%8F%E4%BB%A5%E9%A9%9A%E4%BA%BA%E9%80%9F%E5%BA%A6%E6%B8%9B%E5%B0%91%E8%88%87%E4%BA%BA%E9%A1%9E%E6%B4%BB%E5%8B%95%E6%81%AF%E6%81%AF%E7%9B%B8%E9%97%9C-11812700.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。而在[[甲殼類|甲殼類]]動物中，最引人注目的是[[聖誕島紅蟹|聖誕島紅蟹]]，它每年會三五成群地遷徙<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.parksaustralia.gov.au/christmas/people-place/red-crabs.html |title=Red Crabs |publisher=Parks Australia |date=2013 |accessdate=2014-06-19 |dead-url=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140703153052/http://parksaustralia.gov.au/christmas/people-place/red-crabs.html |archivedate=2014-07-03 }}</ref>，更會在大街馬路上橫行，以等待[[雨水|雨水]]、[[月亮|月亮]]和[[潮汐|潮汐]]連成一線的一刻產卵繁殖<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hk01.com/即時國際/139693/澳洲聖誕島紅蟹大遷徙-大街馬路-橫行霸道-google街景有得睇|title=澳洲聖誕島紅蟹大遷徙 大街馬路「橫行霸道」 Google街景有得睇|first=|last=馮翠山|date=2017-12-08|website=香港01|access-date=2020-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200804074901/https://www.hk01.com/%E5%8D%B3%E6%99%82%E5%9C%8B%E9%9A%9B/139693/%E6%BE%B3%E6%B4%B2%E8%81%96%E8%AA%95%E5%B3%B6%E7%B4%85%E8%9F%B9%E5%A4%A7%E9%81%B7%E5%BE%99-%E5%A4%A7%E8%A1%97%E9%A6%AC%E8%B7%AF-%E6%A9%AB%E8%A1%8C%E9%9C%B8%E9%81%93-google%E8%A1%97%E6%99%AF%E6%9C%89%E5%BE%97%E7%9D%87|archive-date=2020-08-04|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==追踪遷徙==
[[File:Monarch_Butterfly_Danaus_plexippus_Tagged_Closeup_3008px.jpg|thumb]]被貼上標籤作為追蹤的对象]]
{{main |{{tsl|en|Animal migration tracking|動物追踪遷徙}}}}
[[科學家|科學家]]會通過跟踪動物的活動來收集對動物遷徙的數據<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.movebank.org/node/857 |title=What is animal tracking? |publisher=Movebank (database of animal tracking data) |accessdate=2014-06-19 |dead-url=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140421001247/https://www.movebank.org/node/857 |archivedate=2014-04-21 }}</ref>。[[世界自然基金會|世界自然基金會]]香港分會在2008年至2010年期間曾與多個機構合作，利用[[GPS|GPS]]追蹤系統監察兩個[[野鴨|野鴨]]品種的遷徙情況，從中了解野鴨從[[香港|香港]][[米埔自然保護區|米埔自然保護區]]往返北方繁殖地的遷徙過程<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wwf.org.hk/?3520/The-10000km-migration-of-Hong-Kongs-ducks-finally-revealed-by-satellite-tracking|title=衛星追蹤研究揭示香港野鴨萬里長征過程|publisher=世界自然基金會|date=2010-12-31|accessdate=2020-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150810124239/https://www.wwf.org.hk/?3520%2FThe-10000km-migration-of-Hong-Kongs-ducks-finally-revealed-by-satellite-tracking|archive-date=2015-08-10|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[香港觀鳥會|香港觀鳥會]]亦曾以｢定位追蹤裝置」研究[[鷺鳥|鷺鳥]]的移動習性，把四隻於[[新界西|新界西]]北魚塘捕捉的小白鷺戴上追蹤器接近一年，確定其中兩隻具季節性遷徙習性的小白鷺以[[安徽省|安徽省]][[合肥市|合肥市]]為繁殖地，另外兩隻小白鷺則全年留港，夏天時仍會留在[[后海灣|后海灣]]的天然泥灘及魚塘棲息和覓食；到了冬季，四隻小白鷺都會回到新界西北魚塘棲息<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cms.hkbws.org.hk/cms/join-us-tw/zh-tw/egret-tracking|title=全港首次以｢定位追蹤裝置」追蹤鷺鳥 研究顯示小白鷺活動範圍狹小 保護魚塘濕地極為重要|first=TANG|last=Vicky|website=Hong Kong Bird Watching Society|access-date=2020-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200804170711/https://cms.hkbws.org.hk/cms/join-us-tw/zh-tw/egret-tracking|archive-date=2020-08-04|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[無線電|無線電]]跟踪標籤可以安裝在包括[[蜻蜓|蜻蜓]]和[[蜜蜂|蜜蜂]]在內的昆蟲身上。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nationalgeographic.com/explorers/projects/tracking-animal-migration/ |title=Tracking Migration of Dragonflies, Sparrows, and Bees |publisher=National Geographic |accessdate=2014-06-19 |dead-url=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140530020304/http://www.nationalgeographic.com/explorers/projects/tracking-animal-migration/ |archivedate=2014-05-30 }}</ref>

==文化==
在人們了解動物遷徙之前，曾經出現了對動物遷徙的各種民間傳說和錯誤理解，以解釋該地區鳥類的「消失」或「到達」。在[[古希臘|古希臘]]，[[亞里斯多德|亞里斯多德]]指出夏天到來時，[[知更鳥|知更鳥]]會變成了[[普通紅尾鴝|普通紅尾鴝]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.earthlife.net/birds/migration1.html |title=The Earthlife Web – What is Bird Migration |dead-url=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090925184210/http://www.earthlife.net/birds/migration1.html |archivedate=2009-09-25 |accessdate=2020-08-02 }}</ref>；歐洲[[中世紀|中世紀]]的[[獸醫|獸醫]]和[[手稿|手稿]]中則指出[[鵝頸藤壺|鵝頸藤壺]]会長得像樹上的水果或從[[浮木|浮木]]上長成<ref>{{cite web |url=http://bestiary.ca/beasts/beast1195.htm |title=Medieval Bestiary – Barnacle Goose |dead-url=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161125024816/http://bestiary.ca/beasts/beast1195.htm |archivedate=2016-11-25 |accessdate=2020-08-02 }}</ref>。[[自然主義|自然主義]]者{{tsl|en|Gilbert White|吉爾伯特·懷特}}亦曾認為，[[燕子|燕子]]也可以在水下埋在泥濘的河岸或空心樹中冬眠<ref>{{cite book |title=Birds Britannica |publisher=Chatto & Windus |author1=Cocker, Mark |author2={{tsl|en|Richard Mabey|理查德·馬比|Richard Mabey}} |year=2005 |page=315 |isbn=978-0-7011-6907-7}}</ref>。

